steps.instruction:
### Starter
1. In a medium bowl, combine the ripe starter with the water and whole wheat flour
2. Mix well, then cover and set aside at room temperature overnight

### Batter
1. Sift the cocoa, malted milk powder, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and sugar into a medium bowl
2. Stir the mixture into the starter with the eggs, melted butter, vanilla, and chocolate chips
3. Place a rack on a baking sheet, put it in your oven, and preheat it to 200°F. Preheat a waffle iron
4. Cook the waffles according to the manufacturer's instructions. (When it's ready, you'll smell chocolate.)
5. Open and remove the waffle; it will feel soft and tender as you take it out
6. Transfer the finished waffles to the oven to stay warm while you cook the remaining batter. The waffles will crisp up as they sit
7. Leftover waffles can be frozen for a few weeks, and reheated in a toaster

#### Tips
- Waffle irons come in all shapes and sizes. This recipe makes 5 cups of batter, so you'll have a better idea of how many you can expect to get. A 7" Belgian style waffle uses about 3/4 cup of batter; a waffle that makes thinner, "standard" waffles uses about 1/2 cup and will yield more finished waffles

ingredients.note: Semisweet or bittersweet; mini chips work best
